results.title: Shell Game
results.description: Storm, Boom Boom, Rictor, Warlock, Wolfsbane are captured by Cameron Hodge in Genosha and stripped of their powers; the other New Mutants team up with the X-Men and X-Factor; Storm, Boom Boom, and Rictor escape; Hodge kills Warlock.

results.title: United We Stand
results.description: Jubilee, Boom Boom, and Rictor defy the Magistrates; the X-teams split up into two groups; Cable, Marvel Girl, Forge, Gambit, and Sunspot confront Hodge, but are captured and stripped of their powers; Wolfsbane is turned into a mutate.

results.title: War
results.description: The X-teams wage all-out war against Hodge, as Storm restores everybody's powers; they gain help from Genegineer and Chief Magistrate Anderson; Boom Boom finds Warlock's ashes; Wolfsbane is de-mutated and becomes more powerful; they all pursue Hodge.

results.title: The Beginning of the End, Part One
results.description: Gideon arranges for the murder of Sunspot's father; Deapool, working for Mr. Tolliver, attacks Cable; Domino defeats him; Cable and Domino plot strategy; Rictor decides to go after Wolfsbane, who stayed in Genosha; Gideon tells Sunspot his father is dead.

results.title: The Beginning of the End, Part Two
results.description: Feral, a Morlock, flees from Masque; Cable invites Warpath to join the New Mutants, and after his village is destroyed by the Hellfire Club he accepts; Gideon convinces Sunspot to leave; Cannonball challenges Cable; Feral and Shatterstar arrive.

results.title: Against the Beyonder... to the Death!
The Cosmic Cannonball Caper
results.description: The New Mutants attend Lila Cheney's concert; Lila is attacked by an alien, and teleports her and Cannonball to her Dyson sphere; Lila, who is trying to steal Earth, is double-crossed; the New Mutants rescue them; Lila composes a love song for Cannonball.

results.title: Why Do We Do These Things We Do?!
results.description: Mojo captures Betsy (giving her new eyes and the name Psylocke), then Wolfsbane, Sunspot, Karma's siblings, and the Bratpack; the New Mutants meet Captain Britain; Cypher merges with Warlock and saves the day; Psylocke decides to stay at Xavier's school.

results.title: Anything You Can Do--!
results.description: The Impossible Man, hoping to have some fun with the X-Men, interrupts the New Mutants in a training session; Warlock and the Impossible Man prove they are kindred spirits, as they chase each other all over the world, trying to out-do one another.

results.title: Mind Games
results.description: The High Evolutionary captures Magma, in the hope of removing her powers; the New Mutants charge to her rescue, along with Magneto and the other members of the Inner Circle of the Hellfire Club.

results.title: If Wishes Were Horses
results.description: Mirage experiments with her new ability to make her images tangible.

results.title: Blood Drawn, Blood Spilt.
results.description: While Wyndam is at work in Wundagore Mountain, Jessica Drew, the son of Wyndam's associate Jonathan Drew, develops radiation poisoning; Jonathan develops a spider-serum to help her recover, but before he can use it, his wife Merriem is murdered.

results.title: Here Be Monsters!
results.description: Ghaur and Llyra steal the Horn of Doom from Namorita; Namorita believes the New Mutants stole it and goes after them; Ghaur blows the horn, which brings a monster that destroys Atlantis; Namorita and the New Mutants recover the horn.

results.title: Gallery of Former Members of the New Mutants
[Gallery of Former Members of the New Mutants, page 2]
A Case of the Cutes
results.description: Ship asks Boom Boom what she thinks of the men in the New Mutants; Boom Boom falls asleep, and dreams that a comic book artist tries to team her up with various male super heroes, and the best match seems to be Franklin Richards!

results.title: Crowned Heads
results.description: Emperor Naga remembers the events which led to his recovery of the Serpent Crown.

results.title: Days of Future Present Part Three
The Once and Future Mutant
results.description: The adult Franklin Richards visits Xavier's School, re-creating it just the way he remembers it, complete with New Mutants; Banshee, the Invisible Woman, Mr. Fantastic, and young Franklin arrive; Ahab attacks; adult and child Franklin confront each other.

results.title: Tribute the Second
results.description: Wolfsbane pays Cypher's grave a visit, and has a rather unorthodox meeting with him.

results.title: Pawns of Senescence
results.description: The Alliance of Evil attacks the school where Artie, Leech, and Wiz Kid go, absorbing energy into Piecemeal; X-Force defeats the Alliance and tracks Genetech, the organization that hired them, to Long Island, where they are challenged by the New Warriors.

results.title: The First Cut
results.description: Freedom Force is sent to Kuwait to rescue a physicist; they are attacked by Desert Sword; Super Sabre is killed.

results.title: Close Encounters of the Mutant Kind
results.description: Ida Fassbender sees Artie, Leech, and Wiz Kid flying in the Wiz Kid's ship and reports it is a UFO; a mob chases them; they meet Ida; she reminds Leech of Annalee; they become friends, and she invites them to visit anytime they want.

results.title: The Utopia Principle
results.description: Squadron Supreme decides that they need to take control of the Government, and solve all of humanities problems.  Nighthawk disagrees, and leaves the Squadron.

results.title: The Dark From Within
results.description: Nighthawk begins to infiltrate the Squadron with his agents.  Quagmire and Dr. Decibel die.

results.title: Blue Eagle at the Mercy of Nighthawk's Renegades!
Betrayal
results.description: Master Menace figures out how to undo the Behavior Modification machine's effects.  Nighthawk begins to use it on members of the Institute of Evil.

results.title: The Dregs of Victory
results.description: Nighthawk's group fights the Squadron, and convinces them to give up their plans.  Nighthawk, Foxfire, Blue Eagle, Pinball, Golden Archer, Lamprey all killed.

results.title: A Small Sacrifice
results.description: Nuke asks Tom Thumb to find a cure for Cancer, to save his dying parents.  Tom Thumb can not do it, but discovers that he has cancer himself.

results.title: Showdown
results.description: Nuke's parents die, Nuke goes crazy.  Dr Spectrum accidentally kills Nuke.

results.title: Change of Heart
results.description: Tom Thumb creates the Behavior Modification machine.  Golden Archer ask Lady Lark to marry him, and uses the Behavior Modification machine on her when she says no.

results.title: Turn-About
results.description: Institute of Evil captures the families of the Squadron.  Squadron frees them and captures the Institute of Evil.

results.title: Inner Circle
results.description: Members of the Institute of Evil are placed in the Behavior Modification Machine, and then join the Squadron.  Golden Archer is expelled for using the machine on Lady Lark.  Amphibian leaves the Squadron.

results.title: Love and Death
results.description: Master Menace retrieves the evil version of Hyperion, and substitutes him for the real one.  Nighthawk begins to create an opposition to the Squadron.

results.title: The Clash
results.description: The Evil Hyperion is killed by the real Hyperion

results.title: Borrowed Time!
results.description: Tom Thumb dies

results.title: 'Til Death Do Us Part!
results.description: Spider-Man tries to remove his alien costume while fighting off the Vulture-inspired Vulturions

results.title: There, But for Fortune!
results.description: Peter Parker assists in Dominic Fortune's search for his old girlfriend Sabbath Raven, while Spider-Man prevents the Shocker from executing Simon Steele's contract on Fortune's life

results.title: Total War (My Enemy's Enemy ..., conclusion)
results.description: The new Enforcers lure Blood Rose into a trap ... a trap which also attracts Spider-Man, Gauntlet and Nightwatch

results.title: The Origin of Nightwatch
results.description: The origin of Nightwatch:  Dr. Kevin Trench receives the Nightwatch costume from his dying future self
